genresAdvancedInfo.name: guitarra andina
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Guitarra Andina is a genre of music that originates from the Andean regions of South America. It is characterized by the use of the guitar as the primary instrument and incorporates traditional Andean instruments like the quena and charango. The music is often accompanied by vocals and tells stories of the Andean people and their culture.
